Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @sweet potato{300%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then cut into 1cm
chips (no need to peel). Place on a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to
coat. Spread out in a single layer—you need them well spaced out to achieve a
crispy finish! When the oven is hot, roast until golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

> Use two baking trays if needed.

Meanwhile, add @diced Irish chicken breast{260%grams}, @breadcrumbs{1%pack} and
half the @aioli{1%sachet} to a #medium bowl{}. Toss to coat the chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Season with pepper.

Arrange chicken in a single layer on another lined baking tray. Drizzle over
@oil{1%tbsp} (double for 4p). Bake on the top shelf of the oven until chicken
is cooked through and crispy, ~{16-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim, then grate the @carrot{1}(trimmed and grated) (no need to peel).
In a #large bowl{}, mix together @red wine vinegar{1%sachet}, @mayo{1%sachet}
and @sugar{1%tsp} (double for 4p). Season with salt and pepper.

Toss the cooked chicken in the @sweet chilli sauce{2%sachets} and remaining
@aioli{1%sachet}. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper.

> TIP: To reduce the heat in this recipe you can use less sweet chilli sauce.

Add the @salad leaves{40%grams} and carrot to the large bowl with the dressing.
Toss to coat. Divide the chicken, sweet potato and salad between plates.